The design is loosly based on Hector 9000 (https://hackaday.io/project/161585-hector-9000)

Design Language (what you are going to use to solve the problems)
Hardware
- extruded aluminium profile (case)
- Dibond (case)
- 3D printed valve
- presurized bottles
- use as much commercially available parts as possible
- food grade silicon tube
- rubber / silicone plug
- tropfblech rund
- load cell / scale to control amount of liquid dispensed
- star trek replicator like design https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/memoryalpha/images/f/fe/Galaxy-class_replicator.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20120725231632&path-prefix=en
- Luftverteiler
Software
- Highlevel Rest API (Mixe Rezep JSON: 
  Cocktail {
            name: String,
            glass: String,
            category: String,
            shaken_not_stirred: Bool,
            ingredients: [
                {
                  "amount": Value,
                  "name": String,
                }
             ]
            garnish: String,
            preparation: String,
        }
- (W)Lan


Design Chokepoints
- Keep pressure in the bottles
- easy cleaning
- valve tightnes
- valve mechanical durability
- electricity 230, 5, 12, 24 V?

Plugs
25x22x17mm
30x24x18mm
